系所簡介 News現在位置：首頁 > 系所簡介



系所簡介行政人員簡介

理念宗旨
       

	 

	 

	        本在職專班以訓練國內農業企業經營人才為主要目的，透過本校跨領域學術研究人才進行推廣教學，有利於教學相長，教師並可將國內農企業發展相關議題，依學生及產業所面臨環境形成研究主題，與指導教授提供的世界學術研究潮流互相結合，尤其著重在農業與自然資源發展政策、農產品廣告與行銷、農企業管理與競爭、鄉村休閒旅遊發展等研究趨勢的理解及應用，並形成可供在國際期刊發表之研究論文，也藉以深入瞭解世界學術與產業發展趨勢。

	 

	 

設立宗旨 
	1、中部地區「農業企業經營管理」相關師資以中興大學最具特色，師資來源包括農資學院(應用經濟學系、動物科學系、食品暨應用生物科技學系、植物病理學系、 生物產業機電工程學系、 土壤環境科學系、園藝系、昆蟲系、生物產業管理研究所及景觀與遊憩學程)及跨院管理學院(企業管理學系及行銷學系)等具實務與理論專業師資，可提供在職生理論與實務相輔相成之教材與教案，有利就讀學生職場競爭力的提升。
	2、中部地區專業農民、農企業及農民組織等之現有人力資源極需新知識的培育，以配合國家農業升級發展政策，尤其在經營管理與行銷、休閒產業發展、加工科技利用及生產環境控管等的人才培育。

	 

教育目標
	培育學生具農業企業經營管理專業知識與實務能力，提供學生與產業實務界交流與合作，及提升學生自主研究能力。
	 

	 

學生核心能力 
	1、進階專業知能
	2、問題分析與邏輯推理
	3、自主學習與創意
	4、溝通與團隊合作

	 

發展定位
	1、厚植農業企業經營管理與農業科學理論與分析基礎。
	2、加強農業企業化經營管理應用能力。
	3、整合農業科學之應用發展。

	 

成立沿革
	農資學院特於99學年度向教育部申請增設「農業企業經營管理碩士在職專班」，針對各大專院校畢業而從事農業與生物科技發展相關工作的在職人員，以進階的農業企業經營管理人才培育為目標，塑造學生產、製、銷的企業化管理與發展理論應用與分析能力，分別設定「農場管理」、「農產加工」、「行銷管理」領域課程，包容兼顧農業科技與技術及經營管理應用之相關課程，與農業實務界學生期待發揮「教學相長」成效，可為農業界培育優良知識經濟人才。

	 

Mission

This master program is designed to provide trainings for professionals from public and private sectors. Our mission is to equip students with professional and practical knowledge of agricultural business management; to provide partnership and collaboration with industry; and to promote independent research. The program enhances students’ competence in ag-industry management, and to integrate theory and practical training in the development of agricultural business.


	 

Curriculum

Major required courses encompass “Agricultural Business Management, Agricultural Economy, Production Control, Agri-tourism, Research Methodology, and Agricultural Business Case Study.” The core courses include:“farm management, produce processing industry, and marketing management and service”. Students gain professional knowledge and capabilities of problem solving, logical thinking, effective communication and team work. Our program provides training for future leaders in agribusiness field.

 

Core Research Topics


Agricultural Business Management: Courses introduce basic concepts and theories related to management. Students gain fundamental comprehension and acquaintance with business management, and learn how to apply them to practical work in agricultural business. Courses enhance students’ ability in planning, organization, leadership, and management. Students learn how the enterprise operates in agricultural business related to human resource, marketing, production, customer service, and accounting.


	 


Farm Management: Courses help students to acquire fundamental and comprehensive knowledge of farming business management. Students will learn the operation modes of different types of farms through field trips to various farm operators.


	 


Food Processing Management: Courses introduce techniques used for agricultural products processing. Those include principles of hot/cold preservation, concentration and dehydration, irradiation, and microwave heating.


	 


International Agricultural Business: Courses introduce the foundation and strategic execution procedures of international enterprises management. Students learn how multinational enterprises execute strategies, and ethical issues related to strategic operation, as such students will be better equipped with international views of agricultural business operation and gain greater capability of applyingtheories to practices in a rapidly changing global environments.


	 

Achievements

The main goal of this Program is to train domestic Agricultural Business elites, and to implement extension education by cross-field academic research experts at the University. This program emphasizes on the applications of agricultural and natural resources and research trends, including policy development, advertisements and marketing of agricultural products, agricultural business management, rural recreation and tourism development.

This professional master program was founded in 2011. Twenty-nine students have graduated as of 2014. All the students trained by this program perform exceptionally well in their jobs. Three of them are currently pursuing their doctoral degree, and a few started their own business related to agriculture. An alumni association was established on October 18, 2014, to build better connections among all students to foster mutual partnership and cooperation.








﻿


    地址：402臺中市南區國光路250號農業推廣中心轉農企業碩專班 電話：04-22840400-28
